story.title: Truth Teller - Episode 1
story.storyDescription: TruthApp: Thank you for participating in a test trial of the Truth Teller App!
story.creator: web-uploader

messages.text: Thank you for participating in a test trial of the Truth Teller App!
It’s time to find out what people REALLY think of you…
I’m not too nervous, I have a pretty good handle on who I am.
Let’s find out. There are only a couple things I need from you…
What three people do you think know you the best?
That’s easy…my mom. Kyle, my boyfriend. And Jess, my best friend.
What three words would you use to describe yourself?
Extroverted. Adventurous. And then probably, caring.
Thank you for your participation! I will reach out in exactly one week with a full report.
That’s it? I have to wait?!
Hello?!
1 week later
Good morning, Courtney!
I have your report…are you ready to see what your three contacts think about you?
YES!
First, you said you were “extroverted.” Here is what I found…
Transcribed conversation between mother and another (name removed) individual:
I’m worried about her, NAME REMOVED. Do you think Courtney’s ready for college?
Of course she is. She’s a straight A student.
I don’t mean academically…
I worry about her moving so far away.
What if she doesn’t make any friends?
Oh come on, she’ll make friends…
She spends so much time by herself…
It might take her a while to open up to people.
And for people to open up to her.
What about Kyle? Her boyfriend. She’ll have him.
I guess but…
I don’t trust that boy.
I know she’s head over heels, but…
I get a bad vibe from him.
You’re just being protective.
Maybe. But I just want to see our daughter succeed.
I’m not sure if this is the right choice.
We can’t shelter her forever.
I know but…
What if college doesn’t work out? Then what will she do?
WHAT THE HELL?!
Transcription paused.
This is MY mom? Are you serious?!
Yes.
How did you get this conversation?
Every phone has a speaker.
I tapped into your mother’s phone in “listening mode.”
I can’t believe this…
Kyle LOVES me. I know that. My mom has never liked him for some reason.
Would you like to listen to a conversation I recorded of Kyle?
YES!
Mom doesn’t know what she’s talking about.
Kyle wouldn’t want me to go to the same college as him if he didn’t love me…
The second trait you ascribed to yourself was “adventurous.” Here’s what I found…
Transcribed conversation between Kyle and another (name removed) individual:
Dude, you excited about college?
Kinda.
Kinda? Going to Columbia has always been your dream.
Yeah, but I feel like there’s still something tying me down…
What do you mean?
You have to keep what I’m about to tell you a secret, okay?
I got you, man.
It’s Courtney.
What about her? She’s going to Columbia too, right?
Right, but that’s the thing…
I don’t want her to.
Why not? Don’t you want to be with her?
That’s what I thought, at first, but…
Now I’m not so sure.
Uh oh. What happened?
The more I learn about her…I just don’t know, man.
What do you mean?
She just isn’t willing to try new things. Or take a risk. At ANYTHING.
Which is fine, I guess. It’s just not my personality.
Are you going to break up with her?
I don’t know. I feel bad. She’s following me to Columbia…
But if you don’t like her—
I know. I know. I’m trying to figure it all out.
ARE YOU KIDDING?!?!
Transcription paused.
I CAN’T believe him!!
I am sorry you are displeased with the results.
Are you, though?!
I am just presenting you with what I have heard.
Well, this sucks…
Thank you for your feedback. Your opinion is important to us.
Wasn’t really feedback for you, but whatever…
I have one more person, right?
Correct, your best friend, Jess.
Jess will come through. I know she will.
The last trait you ascribed to yourself was “caring.” Here’s what I found…
Transcribed conversation between Jess and another (name removed) individual:
Anyone you going to miss when you leave?
Not really. Ready to get out of this stupid town.
Not even your best friend?
Who’s my best friend?
I don’t remember her name…
Who’s that girl you always walk home from school with?
Courtney?
Yeah!
Oh God, no. I won’t miss her. Don’t tell her, though…
Why not? You two hang out all the time.
Not my choice. It’s because she’s clingy.
And I feel bad. That’s why I hang out with her.
Plus, she always asks to borrow my stuff or calls me when she feels insecure about Kyle.
It’s annoying.
Then when I need something, she doesn’t respond…
I can’t have that energy around me anymore.
That’s why I’m saying “bye, forever” to her after graduation.
Ouch, that’s harsh.
Well, it’s real life.
OK! STOP! PLEASE!
Transcription paused.
This is HORRIBLE.
I am sorry you’ve had a bad experience with the app.
This is all real? I mean real conversations?
Yes.
Oh, God.
Your test trial has ended. Would you recommend this app to others?
NO!
I am sorry again—
OH SHUT UP!
Courtney closes the app.
Then, thinking out loud to herself…
I feel like I don’t even know these people…
Kyle and I need to chat…
Then Jess.
I can do this.
1 year later
Hello Courtney.
You again?
We are offering all our test trial subjects another opportunity to use the newly updated app for FREE!
I’m not sure I want to subject myself to that again.
I am sorry to hear that. May I ask why not?
Hearing what people say about me behind closed doors?
It didn’t exactly feel good.
I am truly regretful that you had such a negative experience.
I guess it wasn’t your fault…
You just brought to light what others were really saying…
You know, it did help me in some ways.
I moved on from some people who weren’t good for me.
I broke up with Kyle. Stopped talking to Jess.
Now I’m going to Cal Tech instead of Columbia. Turned out to be a better fit actually.
I guess now that I think about it, I would actually like to take you up on your offer.
GREAT! Just like last time, what three people do you think know you best?
I can autofill with the same three people you picked last time—
No…I’d like to choose two new people. Keep my mom as one…
My new boyfriend, Quinn, and my roommate, Lila.
What three words would you use to describe yourself?
I want to try the same three I used last time.
Extroverted, Adventurous, and Caring?
Yep.
I will report back to you in a week!
Looking forward to it…
1 week later
Hello Courtney!
I have another report…are you ready to see what your three contacts think about you?
Bring it on.
The first trait is “extroverted.” Here is what I found…
Transcribed conversation between mother and another (name removed) individual:
I’m so happy for Courtney.
She’s really come into her own since going off to college.
That’s wonderful!
She’s excelling academically and really involved in extracurriculars.
She seems so happy now. Always has a smile on her face.
I honestly never thought she’d love Cal Tech as much as she does.
Are you disappointed she didn’t go to Columbia? It’s such a prestigious school.
Oh no, I’m glad she didn’t pick that place. She made the right choice for sure.
She’s making new friends I take it?
Oh, yes. She has a delightful roommate. They hang out all the time.
And she’s got a new boyfriend…I think this one’s a keeper.
Oh, Mom…
Transcription paused.
Would you like me to keep playing the transcription?
No, I get the gist of it.
Shall we move on to Quinn?
Go ahead.
The second trait was “adventurous.” Here’s what I found…
Transcribed conversation between Quinn and another (name removed) individual:
So how are things going with the new girl?
Oh man. She’s awesome.
She’s a gamer like me, which is a big plus.
And I like that she doesn’t care if we go out or like…do big, fancy things for dates.
We’re both cool with just staying in and watching Netflix—
Just hanging out together.
I think I may throw-up…
Oh, shut up. You’re just jealous.
So I wouldn’t say I’m adventurous but…
I’m okay with that. Quinn likes me for who I am.
Transcription paused.
Let me hear the last person?
Of course. The last trait is “caring.” Here’s what I found…
Transcribed conversation between Lila and another (name removed) individual:
So how’s roomie life?
I’m so lucky. Courtney and I clicked right away.
And, we have the same birthday.
Nice. What’s she like?
She was a little shy at first, but once I got to know her…
She’s really sweet.
I mean, when Tyler dumped me, she was the first one there for me.
I can’t believe he dragged you to Cal Tech just to break up with you in the middle of the first semester.
I know…I wanted to go home, but Courtney saved me.
She told me what happened with her boyfriend from high school…
She made me feel so much better about it all.
I’m glad you lucked out…my freshman roommate was a terror.
Well, you can’t have her. We’re going to be roomies again next year.
Is my status as best friend being threatened?
Haha, I don’t know…she’s giving you a run for your money.
I think I have all I need to know.
Transcription paused.
This ends your free trial of the newly updated app. Would you like to buy a subscription?
Thank you, but I don’t think I’ll be using this app again.
I am sorry you are displeased with your experience.
It’s not that…
I’ve just learned that…you can’t label yourself with just three words…
And the people we surround ourselves with get that.
So I guess I’m thanking you.
Courtney deletes the Truth Teller App.
